President Donald Trump has designated certain funding as emergency requirements in accordance with section 114(b) of division A of the Continuing Appropriations Act, 2021 and Other Extensions Act (H.R. 8337). This designation includes all funding designated by Congress in the Act pursuant to section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. This statement was issued to the Congress of the United States on October 1, 2020, from the White House.